WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.316 --> 00:00:03.029
VA is a customer service organization

2
00:00:03.029 --> 00:00:05.857
and our primary mission is to serve Veterans

3
00:00:05.857 --> 00:00:07.635
and their families.

4
00:00:07.635 --> 00:00:10.978
VA serves the population of 26 million Veterans

5
00:00:10.978 --> 00:00:14.161
and their spouses, survivors, and dependents.

6
00:00:14.161 --> 00:00:16.621
And nearly 3/4 of these living Veterans

7
00:00:16.621 --> 00:00:19.872
served during a war or period of conflict.

8
00:00:19.872 --> 00:00:23.341
VA also serves a growing number of women Veterans.

9
00:00:23.341 --> 00:00:26.861
Currently there are 1.7 million women Veterans,

10
00:00:26.861 --> 00:00:30.717
or 7% of the total population of Veterans.

11
00:00:30.717 --> 00:00:32.958
About 1/4 of the nation's population

12
00:00:32.958 --> 00:00:36.083
is potentially eligible for VA benefits.

13
00:00:36.083 --> 00:00:39.123
VA's responsibility to care for those who serve

14
00:00:39.123 --> 00:00:42.844
can last a lifetime, or far beyond a lifetime.

15
00:00:42.844 --> 00:00:45.386
The last dependent of a Revolutionary War

16
00:00:45.386 --> 00:00:47.746
Veteran died in 1911.

17
00:00:47.746 --> 00:00:52.158
The last Veteran of the Spanish-American War died in 1992.

18
00:00:52.158 --> 00:00:55.871
152 children and widows of the Spanish-American War

19
00:00:55.871 --> 00:00:59.603
still receive VA compensation or pension benefits.

20
00:00:59.603 --> 00:01:01.563
Five children of Civil War Veterans

21
00:01:01.563 --> 00:01:03.730
still receive VA benefits.

